      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound example of the analog driving experience. Powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, the engine pulls cleanly through the rev range with a linear power delivery. The 6-speed G96 manual transaxle offers precise throws, while the chassis retains its factory-spec composure thanks to well-maintained multi-link rear suspension and McPherson struts. Crucial preventative maintenance has been addressed, including an IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback typical of this era, and the four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers ensure consistent thermal management and stopping power. While displaying minor aesthetic patina from regular use, the structural integrity and drivetrain performance remain excellent for the spirited driver.",
